https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/tvdrRA9weSeqShkH9SvrYvXSlYL.jpg Intangible Blue is a portrait of the beauty and biodiversity of Mexico’s seas and coasts. It shows people struggling both on and off shore to develop an exemplary sustainable model. It is a voyage through the country’s northeastern seas, offering a new perspective on the interaction that can exist between oceans and city dwellers, to achieve a balance between resource management and preservation.
